              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The most forward two counters were telescopes",
                " consisting of dE-E silicon surface barrier detectors",
                " while the other four counters consisted of single",
                " E-detectors. An overall energy resolution of",
                " 70-80 keV was obtained for the three reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "46Ti and 50Ti targets were prepared by rolling Ti metal",
                " down to thicknesses of 333 microg/cm2 and 269",
                " microg/cm2, respectively. The 48Ti target was prepared",
                " by reducing and evaporating TiO as a self-supporting",
                " 48Ti target of thickness 60 microg/cm2.",
                " Isotopic composition of the 46,48,50Ti targets:",
                " Target   46Ti   47Ti   48Ti   49Ti   50Ti",
                " 46Ti     81.2    2.1   14.1   1.5     1.1   percent",
                " 48Ti      0.25   0.26  99.13  0.19    0.17  percent",
                " 50Ti      2.0    1.8   17.8   2.0    76.4   percent"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The alpha-particles were detected using 6 counters",
                " at angular intervals of 10 degree"
